INFO.name: query
INFO.value: SELECT ivoa.obscore.dataproduct_type, ivoa.obscore.dataproduct_subtype, ivoa.obscore.calib_level, ivoa.obscore.obs_collection, ivoa.obscore.obs_id, ivoa.obscore.obs_title, ivoa.obscore.obs_publisher_did, ivoa.obscore.obs_creator_did, ivoa.obscore.access_url, ivoa.obscore.access_format, ivoa.obscore.access_estsize, ivoa.obscore.target_name, ivoa.obscore.target_class, ivoa.obscore.s_ra, ivoa.obscore.s_dec, ivoa.obscore.s_fov, ivoa.obscore.s_region, ivoa.obscore.s_resolution, ivoa.obscore.t_min, ivoa.obscore.t_max, ivoa.obscore.t_exptime, ivoa.obscore.t_resolution, ivoa.obscore.em_min, ivoa.obscore.em_max, ivoa.obscore.em_res_power, ivoa.obscore.o_ucd, ivoa.obscore.pol_states, ivoa.obscore.facility_name, ivoa.obscore.instrument_name FROM ivoa.obscore WHERE dataproduct_type = 'cube' AND obs_collection = 'CALIFA' LIMIT 2000

RESOURCE.INFO: Definition and support code for the ObsCore data model and table.
The IVOA-defined obscore table, containing generic metadata for datasets within this datacenter.

TABLE.name: obscore
TABLE.DESCRIPTION: The IVOA-defined obscore table, containing generic metadata for datasets within this datacenter.

GROUP.name: note-calib
GROUP.DESCRIPTION:
The calib_level flag takes the following values:
=== =========================================================== 0 Raw Instrumental data requiring instrument-specific tools 1 Instrumental data processable with standard tools 2 Calibrated, science-ready data without instrument signature 3 Enhanced data products (e.g., mosaics) === ===========================================================

FIELD.name: dataproduct_type
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: High level scientific classification of the data product, taken from an enumeration

FIELD.name: dataproduct_subtype
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Data product specific type

FIELD.name: calib_level
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Amount of data processing that has been applied to the data

FIELD.name: obs_collection
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Name of a data collection (e.g., project name) this data belongs to

FIELD.name: obs_id
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier for an observation

FIELD.name: obs_title
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Free-from title of the data set

FIELD.name: obs_publisher_did
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Dataset identifier assigned by the publisher.

FIELD.name: obs_creator_did
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Dataset identifier assigned by the creator.

FIELD.name: access_url
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The URL at which to obtain the data set.

FIELD.name: access_format
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: MIME type of the resource at access_url

FIELD.name: access_estsize
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Estimated size of data product

FIELD.name: target_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Object a targeted observation targeted

FIELD.name: target_class
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Class of the target object (star, QSO, ...; use Simbad object classification http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim-display?data=otypes if at all possible)

FIELD.name: s_ra
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: RA of (center of) observation, ICRS

FIELD.name: s_dec
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Dec of (center of) observation, ICRS

FIELD.name: s_fov
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Approximate spatial extent for the region covered by the observation

FIELD.name: s_region
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Region covered by the observation, as a polygon

FIELD.name: s_resolution
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Best spatial resolution within the data set

FIELD.name: t_min
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Lower bound of times represented in the data set, as MJD

FIELD.name: t_max
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Upper bound of times represented in the data set, as MJD

FIELD.name: t_exptime
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total exporure time

FIELD.name: t_resolution
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Minimal significant time interval along the time axis

FIELD.name: em_min
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Minimal wavelength represented within the data set

FIELD.name: em_max
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Maximal wavelength represented within the data set

FIELD.name: em_res_power
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Spectral resolving power delta lambda/lamda

FIELD.name: o_ucd
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: UCD for the product's observable

FIELD.name: pol_states
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: List of polarization states in the data set

FIELD.name: facility_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Name of the facility at which data was taken

FIELD.name: instrument_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Name of the instrument that produced the data
